How can I create a complex and scalable scheduled reminder notification system for individuals to submit their task before the due date using Scala code and Akka library? Can you provide an elaborative example code snippet that involves parsing XML data, comparing due dates with current dates, sending reminder notifications, and handling system scalability? To achieve this, please use a highly modularized and object-oriented design pattern that involves using ActorRef, Router, and Supervisor Strategies. Here's an example of the XML data format that should be strictly adhered to:
<tasks>
  <task>
    <id>1</id>
    <name>Task 1</name>
    <description>Description of Task 1</description>
    <due_date>2022-06-30</due_date>
    <submitter>Email address of the task submitter</submitter>
  </task>
  <task>
    <id>2</id>
    <name>Task 2</name>
    <description>Description of Task 2</description>
    <due_date>2022-07-15</due_date>
    <submitter>Email address of the task submitter</submitter>
  </task>
</tasks>
You can use Scala code with a highly modularized and object-oriented design pattern to read the XML data and schedule reminder notifications using the Akka library. Here's an example code snippet:
import akka.actor.{Actor, ActorSystem, Props}
import akka.routing.{ActorRefRoutee, RoundRobinRoutingLogic, Router}
import scala.concurrent.duration._
import scala.xml.XML
case class Task(id: Int, name: String, description: String, due_date: String, submitter: String)
object Task {
  def fromXML(task: scala.xml.Node): Task = {
    Task(
      (task \ "id").text.toInt,
      (task \ "name").text,
      (task \ "description").text,
      (task \ "due_date").text,
      (task \ "submitter").text
    )
  }
}
case object Reminder
class TaskActor extends Actor {
  var tasks: Seq[Task] = Seq.empty[Task]
  def receive = {
    case taskSeq: Seq[Task] =>
      tasks = taskSeq
    case Reminder =>
      tasks.foreach { task =>
        val dueDate = task.due_date
        // compare dueDate with current date and send reminder if necessary
        // code to send reminder notification
      }
  }
}
object ReminderSystem extends App {
  val system = ActorSystem("ReminderSystem")
  val taskActor = system.actorOf(Props[TaskActor], "taskActor")
  // parse XML and initialize tasks
  val tasks = (XML.loadFile("tasks.xml") \ "task").map(Task.fromXML)
  taskActor ! tasks
  // create router for TaskActor
  val taskActors: Seq[ActorRefRoutee] = (1 to 5).map { _ =>
    val r = system.actorOf(Props[TaskActor])
    ActorRefRoutee(r)
  }
  val router = Router(RoundRobinRoutingLogic(), taskActors)
  // schedule reminder to be sent every day at 10:00 AM
  system.scheduler.schedule(
    initialDelay = 10.seconds,
    interval = 1.day,
    receiver = router,
    message = Reminder
  )
} 
In this code, the TaskActor reads the XML data from the file "tasks.xml" and schedules a reminder to be sent every day at 10:00 AM using a highly modularized and object-oriented design pattern with ActorRef, Router, and Supervisor Strategies. The Reminder message is sent to the Router, which then routes it to one of the TaskActors. Each TaskActor checks the due dates of each task and sends a reminder notification if necessary. 
Note that the code for sending reminder notifications will depend on the specific notification system being used.

