Next, we sort the data by income in ascending order and calculate the cumulative percentage of people and cumulative percentage of income. We use these values to calculate the Gini coefficient, which measures income inequality.
Finally, we print the results and plot the Lorenz curve. The Lorenz curve is a graphical representation of income inequality, with the cumulative percentage of people on the x-axis and the cumulative percentage of income on the y-axis.
