As an AI assistant, I can provide you with an overview of how blockchain technology can be integrated into your restaurant business operations to streamline processes, enhance customer experience, and improve security.
Menu Management:
One way to use blockchain technology for menu management is by creating smart contracts that automatically update prices and availability of items on the menu. This can help to eliminate errors and reduce the time and effort required to manually update the menu. The following code can be used to create a smart contract for menu management:
```
pragma solidity ^0.4.17;
contract Menu {
    struct MenuItem {
        string name;
        uint256 price;
        bool available;
    }
    mapping (uint256 => MenuItem) public menuItems;
    uint256 public itemCount;
    function addMenuItem(string _name, uint256 _price) public {
        menuItems[itemCount] = MenuItem(_name, _price, true);
        itemCount++;
    }
    function removeMenuItem(uint256 _itemId) public {
        menuItems[_itemId].available = false;
    }
    function updateMenuItemPrice(uint256 _itemId, uint256 _price) public {
        menuItems[_itemId].price = _price;
    }
}
```
Payment Processing:
Another way to integrate blockchain technology into your restaurant business is by allowing customers to pay using cryptocurrencies. This can be done by creating a wallet address that customers can send their payments to. The following code can be used to generate a wallet address:
